ora borealis and the white nights of the North. Crucially, he offers a description of the Viking Rus, including their customs, clothing, body painting, and a striking account of a ship funeral. Together, these anecdotes illuminate a vibrant world of diversity during the heyday of the Abbasid Empire, narrated with as much curiosity and zeal as they were perceived by its observant beholder.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aBulgars (Turkic people)zRussia (Federation)zVolga River RegionxHistory. 0aIbn Faḍlān, Aḥmad,dactive 922xTravelzAsia, Central. 0aIbn Faḍlān, Aḥmaddactive 922xTravelzAsia, Central. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh1 aMontgomery, James E.1 aSeverin, Tim.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831107289720 cprintz978147989989040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479826698423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479826698/original  a978-3-11-072897-2  New York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK